Key Match Events: Fullkrug scored the first goal for Germany in the 27th minute.
Musiala scored the second goal for Germany in the 58th minute.
Wirtz scored the third goal for Germany in the 66th minute.
Pavlovic scored the fourth goal for Germany in the 77th minute.
Havertz scored the fifth goal for Germany with a penalty in the 81st minute.
Nego received a yellow card in the 9th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Several stars stepped down following Germany's exit from Euro 2024, leading to a new-look side for the Nations League.
Julian Nagelsmann remains the coach for Germany after their quarter-final exit in Euro 2024.
Joshua Kimmich has been appointed as Germany's captain.
Germany's possible starting lineup includes Ter Stegen, Kimmich, Schlotterbeck, Tah, Mittelstadt, Gross, Pavlovic, Musiala, Wirtz, Fuhrich, and Havertz.
Hungary's possible starting lineup includes Gulacsi, Botka, Orban, M. Dardai, Bolla, A. Nagy, Schafer, Kerkez, Sallai, Szoboszlai, and Varga.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany's dream of lifting the European Championship trophy on home soil ended in the quarter-finals of Euro 2024.
Hungary missed out on a place in the knockout phase of Euro 2024 due to goal difference.
Hungary had lost just once in 16 games heading into the Euros.
Germany has not progressed beyond the group phase in three previous Nations League attempts.
